                    </div>
                    <span>My review is truly biased toward my personal needs-first off.  With subject matter in regards to change, I would rather prefer cold hard facts.
<br />
<br />Williamson's voice in this recording is soothing as she addresses the audience.  However, the over-flowery content in this book leads me to sleep rather than pay attention. Williamson sounds more like a meditation instructor than an expert of metaphysical studies.  However, the text probably has better meaning if you read the book instead.   
<br />
<br />This book is more for the emotive idealist.  Sounds soothing but not enough hard facts for people with harder hearts like myself.   </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A thinking person's guide</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
